children.subject: How much time commitment was 61BL weekly? Did you end up doing well in the class?

If you are doing Hilfinger version of projects, it would take like 20 hours per week for a normal semester, but I'm not sure about the summer version because it seems like it may cut on some materials? It also depends on how much programming experience you had before. I've seen people inputting less than 10 hours each week during normal semester because they just understand questions and solve them at a much faster rate. 

Generally 61B will take up a lot of time because it has hw, lab and some really chunky projects, the final project Gitlet (if you are taking it) may take you like 70 - 80 hours from the design phase to implementing all the codes. Other than doing manual coding, you also have to put in some time to have a better understanding of the concepts in data structure if you want to perform well in tests.

I did CS 61BL and Math 54 together last summer and ended up spending almost all my time on 61BL. Not sure what the workload of 53 is but it's almost certainly going to be much less than 61BL. Taking another tech alongside 61BL is doable but probably not recommended.

<md>I took W53 last summer with Hutchings alongside a low commitment 2 unit class, AFX, and my sports team. 53 took up decent chunks of time but I felt it was manageable with all my activities. Not sure about 61BL workload, but since past 61B have stated 3-5+ hours per day, it might be a lot to cram 53 homework and lectures as well. 53 had weekly quizzes and psets, but no midterms. If you stay on track, you could probably handle it assuming you don't have any other major commitments.</md>
